HEADWORD: Triskele
<hw>Tris"kele</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
three-legged. See <er>Tri-</er>; <er>Isosceles</er>.]</ety> <def>A
figure composed of three branches, usually curved, radiating from a
center, as the figure composed of three human legs, with bent knees,
which has long been used as a badge or symbol of <geog>Sicily</geog> and
of the <geog>Isle of Man</geog>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

